Vice President Biden called Serbian President Tadic to discuss the upcoming advisory opinion of the International Court of Justice on Kosovo's declaration of independence. Biden expressed full support for a democratic and multi-ethnic Kosovo, and reiterated the United States' commitment to Kosovo's sovereignty and territorial integrity. He urged the Serbian government to work constructively with Kosovo to improve the lives of the people in the region. Biden also praised the bilateral cooperation between the US and Serbia and commended Serbia's efforts to improve relations with Croatia and Bosnia and Herzegovina. He also welcomed Serbia's commitment to cooperate with the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia.